Description:
    Generates a feature file to manage a feature of the app

Example:
    bin/rails generate rails_feature_flip:feature Thing enabled:boolean foo bar

    With default values:
    bin/rails generate rails_feature_flip:feature Thing enabled:boolean foo --defaults enabled:false foo:bar

    This will create:
        config/features/thing_feature.rb

    Then in application.rb:
        config.x.features.thing = Features::ThingFeature.new(enabled: false, foo: 'bar')
    With that you can use:
        App.features.thing.enabled?
        # => false
        App.features.thing.foo
        # => bar
